's not active. I'll also want to ensure we avoid Mockito mocks within native tests due to potential issues with inline access.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining constructor instantiation**\\n\\nI'm considering how to instantiate a package-private or private constructor effectively. I think including methods, getters, and setters will cover what I need. The static initializer in the active class is triggered when the InstrumentationMemberAccessor is first created from Plugins. If I call Plugins.getMemberAccessor directly, that might trigger it too. However, I’m concerned that the public top-level test currently imports the internal Plugins, which could be an issue for my setup. I need to ensure the mapping aligns properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dBCJAe8wyMQvSW8qrEazawdt|fc_0b946e4e9a68fff90169f96daeee64819fb8e58035cf6d89ed", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InstrumentationMemberAccessorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.mockito.InjectMocks;\nimport org.mockito.Mock;\nimport org.mockito.MockitoAnnotations;\n", "newText": "import org.mockito.InjectMocks;\nimport org.mockito.Mock;\nimport org.mockito.MockitoAnnotations;\nimport org.mockito.internal.util.reflection.ModuleMemberAccessor;\nimport org.mockito.plugins.MemberAccessor;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void annotationInitializationUsesInstrumentationMemberAccessorForMembers() throws Exception {\n        try (AutoCloseable mocks = MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this)) {\n            when(collaborator.message()).thenReturn(\"instrumented\");\n\n            assertThat(constructorInjectedService.message()).isEqualTo(\"instrumented\");\n            assertThat(setterInjectedService.message()).isEqualTo(\"instrumented\");\n            assertThat(setterInjectedService.setterWasUsed()).isTrue();\n            verify(collaborator, times(2)).message();\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void annotationInitializationUsesInstrumentationMemberAccessorForMembers() throws Exception {\n        try (AutoCloseable mocks = MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this)) {\n            when(collaborator.message()).thenReturn(\"instrumented\");\n\n            assertThat(constructorInjectedService.message()).isEqualTo(\"instrumented\");\n            assertThat(setterInjectedService.message()).isEqualTo(\"instrumented\");\n            assertThat(setterInjectedService.setterWasUsed()).isTrue();\n            verify(collaborator, times(2)).message();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void moduleMemberAccessorAccessesPrivateConstructorsMethodsAndFields() throws Exception {\n        MemberAccessor accessor = new ModuleMemberAccessor();\n        Constructor<PrivateTarget> constructor =\n                PrivateTarget.class.getDeclaredConstructor(String.class);\n        PrivateTarget target = (PrivateTarget) accessor.newInstance(constructor, \"created\");\n\n        Field value = PrivateTarget.class.getDeclaredField(\"value\");\n        assertThat(accessor.get(value, target)).isEqualTo(\"created\");\n\n        accessor.set(value, target, \"updated\");\n        assertThat(accessor.get(value, target)).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n\n        Method describe = PrivateTarget.class.getDeclaredMethod(\"describe\", String.class);\n        assertThat(accessor.invoke(describe, target, \"prefix\")).isEqualTo(\"prefix:updated\");\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "    static class SetterInjectedService {\n        private Collaborator collaborator;\n        private boolean setterWasUsed;\n\n        public void setCollaborator(Collaborator collaborator) {\n            this.collaborator = collaborator;\n            setterWasUsed = true;\n        }\n\n        String message() {\n            return collaborator.message();\n        }\n\n        boolean setterWasUsed() {\n            return setterWasUsed;\n        }\n    }\n\n}\n", "newText": "    static class SetterInjectedService {\n        private Collaborator collaborator;\n        private boolean setterWasUsed;\n\n        public void setCollaborator(Collaborator collaborator) {\n            this.collaborator = collaborator;\n            setterWasUsed = true;\n        }\n\n        String message() {\n            return collaborator.message();\n        }\n\n        boolean setterWasUsed() {\n            return setterWasUsed;\n        }\n    }\n\n    static class PrivateTarget {\n        private String value;\n\n        private PrivateTarget(String value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n\n        private String describe(String prefix) {\n            return prefix + \":\" + value;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1084, "output": 1897, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32165, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777954207312, "responseId": "resp_0b946e4e9a68fff90169f96d9fc26c819fa50cabfcb2b491f6"}}
